gomodel:SYNGO_891  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Profilin-1 is detected in the the presynapse of rat hippocampus CA1 [Fig3D] and cerebellar cortex [Fig4B & C] as well as the spine in CA1 [Fig3B-D]. The presentence profilin-1 at both the pre- and postsynaptic side was also observed in cultured mouse hippocampal neurons [Fig 5A-C]. The localisation of the immuno-gold label are consistent with the role of profilins as actin regulators.. Experimental description: Figure 3 and 4 is rat tissue \"Adult albino rats (Wistar) were deeply anaesthetized with ketamine (100 mg / kg) and xylazine (5 mg / kg) and perfused through the left ventricle\", Figure 5 is mouse cultured neurons \"Primary cultures of hippocampal neurons were prepared from C57Bl6J mice at postnatal days 0-1 as described previously\" found in the material and methods" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-5259-4945" ;
        dc:date           "2017-08-07" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_891" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .
